1. Prefer to use as less 3rd party dependencies as possible and iff needed, use a dependency that is LTS version and has no known vulnerabilities.
2. Prefer reading the codebase and understanding the functionality before starting to code.
3. Prefer Test driven development
4. Use design principles judiciously to arrive at a solution. Prefer clean interfaces and Responsibility segregation
5. create frequent commits.
6. Every repo and codebase must have pre-commit hooks that will lint, security check, build the codebase
7. We use vitest for test